tidy_pop <- gather(messy_pop, 'year', 'pop', -country)

  head(4)

1.4 Building a plot

1.4.1 Calling ggplot()

ggplot(tidy_pop)

1.4.2 Adding aesthetics

ggplot(tidy_pop,
  aes(x = year, #<<
      y = pop) #<<
  )

1.4.3 Choosing the geometry (geom)

ggplot(tidy_pop,
  aes(x = year,
      y = pop)
  ) +
  geom_point()

1.4.4 Adding a third variable, country, as a colour.

ggplot(tidy_pop,
  aes(x = year,
      y = pop,
      color = country) 
  ) + 
  geom_point()

1.4.5 Adding a line to the plot

ggplot(tidy_pop,
  aes(x = year,
      y = pop,
      color = country) 
  ) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line()
## geom_path: Each group consists of only one observation. Do you need to
## adjust the group aesthetic?

1.4.6 Adding a line to the plot, group by country.

ggplot(tidy_pop,
  aes(x = year,
      y = pop,
      color = country) 
  ) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(
    aes(group = country))

1.4.7 Storing a plot

g <- ggplot(tidy_pop, 
  aes(x = year,
      y = pop,
      color = country) 
  ) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(
    aes(group = country))

g

1.4.8 Specifying the aesthetics for each geometry.

g <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(
    data = tidy_pop, 
    aes(x = year, 
      y = pop, 
      color = country) 
  ) +
  geom_line(
    data = tidy_pop, 
    aes(x = year, 
      y = pop, 
      color = country, 
      group = country) 
    )

g

1.4.9 Adding more data. Creating tidy_pop2

tidy_pop2 <- left_join(tidy_pop, select(gapminder, country, continent))
## Joining, by = "country"
g <- ggplot(tidy_pop2) +
  aes(x = year,
      y = pop,
      color = country) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(group = country))

1.4.10 Using Facets

g + facet_wrap(~ country)

1.4.11 Using facet_grid, two variables.

g + facet_grid(continent ~ country)

1.4.12 Adding labels

(g <- g + labs(x = "Year", y = "Population (millions)"))

1.4.13 Showing coordinates

g + coord_flip()

1.4.14 Changing the color scale

g + scale_color_manual(values = c("peru", "pink", "plum"))

1.4.15 Changing the scale of the y

g + scale_y_log10()

1.4.16 Changing the scale of the x

g + scale_x_discrete(labels = c("MCMXCVII", "MMII", "MMVII"))

1.4.17 Changing the theme

g + theme_bw()

1.4.18 Changing the theme (fonts and colours)

g + theme_bw() + theme(text = element_text(colour = "hotpink", size = 20))

1.4.19 Setting an overall theme:

my_theme <- theme_bw() +
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "Palatino", size = 12),
    panel.border = element_rect(colour = 'grey80'), 
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank()
  )

theme_set(my_theme)

1.4.20 Making the plot with the new theme
